/* MasterClass stuff */
insert into consumption(consumption_venue, format, live_watch, primary_language, item, url, start_date, start_date_precision, end_date, end_date_precision, notes) values
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Chris Voss Teaches the Art of Negotiation','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/chris-voss-teaches-the-art-of-negotiation','2020-04-05','day','2020-04-06','day','This class was one of the main motivators for me to sign up for MasterClass. The content seems relevant enough to many day-to-day situations and I expect it''ll influence my real-world behavior. It generally lived up to my expectations. I believe that a single listening was enough for me to absorb and retain almost everything. I also downloaded and saved the workbook. I would later write a lengthy review https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/CRAzG386t3suSqDgd/chris-voss-negotiation-masterclass-review of the MasterClass.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Howard Schultz: Business Leadership','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/howard-schultz-leading-a-values-based-business','2020-04-06','day','2020-04-07','day','This class was reasonably interesting, though it may not be too applicable to my life as I''m not (currently) leading a company or growing a business of the sort his lesson was focused on. Schultz drew on his experience growing Starbucks into an international business to give general business advice. Not everything clicked with me. I may watch parts of it again. I also downloaded and saved the workbook.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Bob Woodward Teaches Investigative Journalism','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/bob-woodward-teaches-investigative-journalism','2020-04-07','day','2020-04-11','day','This class was reasonably interesting, though it may not be too applicable to my life, since I am not an investigative journalist. Nonetheless, it''s interesting to compare the spirit of his principles with the principles behind other investigative work and content creation that I do. I may watch parts of it again. I also downloaded and saved the workbook.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Daniel Elfman Teaches Music for Film','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/danny-elfman-teaches-music-for-film','2020-04-11','day','2021-06-27','day','I watched a little bit of this in 2020, then switched away from it for a while once I started watching Sara Blakely''s MasterClass. I resumed on 2021-06-06 and finished it this time. There were a lot of similarities with Hans Zimmer''s MasterClass (that was also about the same subject) but there was enough difference in topics and focus that watching both didn''t feel redundant.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Bob Iger Teaches Business Strategy and Leadership','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/bob-iger-teaches-business-strategy-and-leadership','2020-04-11','day','2020-05-01','month','This class was reasonably interesting, though not everything clicked with me. Overall, I found it less interesting and relevant than the classes by Howard Schultz and Sara Blakely. I do not remember exactly when I finished this class, but it was some time in May 2020, likly just before starting the Axelrod and Rove MasterClass.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Sara Blakely Teaches Self-Made Entrepreneurship','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/sara-blakely-teaches-self-made-entrepreneurship','2020-04-11','day','2020-04-18','day','This class was reasonably interesting, though not everything clicked with me. I may watch parts of it again. I also downloaded and saved the workbook.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','David Axelrod and Karl Rove Teach Campaign Strategy and Messaging','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/david-axelrod-and-karl-rove-teach-campaign-strategy-and-messaging','2020-05-09','day','2020-05-16','day','I started this class out of curiosity. When starting, I was curious if this would increase my disdain of politics or give me newfound appreciation for it. Ultimately, I became more appreciative of the skill and art of political campaigning, but remained as skeptical as before about the correlation between performance on the electoral "test" and the real work of governance.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Natalie Portman Teaches Acting','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/natalie-portman-teaches-acting','2020-05-16','day','2020-05-23','day','I started this class mainly out of idle curiosity. I found it reasonably interesting, though not too relevant. It was interesting to see the emphasis on playfulness given by Portman.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','#MasterClassLive with Chris Voss','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nZcBuSCT3Io','2020-05-23','day','2020-05-23','day','I watched this MasterClass Q&A session two months aftere it was aired live; this is a complement to Voss''s Art of Negotiation MasterClass.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Paul Krugman Teaches Economics and Society','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/paul-krugman-teaches-economics-and-society','2020-05-23','day','2020-05-30','day','I watched this out of curiosity. Paul Krugman is an eminent economist but has different ideological leanings than I do, and has also been accused of writing biased and sloppy stuff (see https://www.econlib.org/archives/2013/12/why_i_read_paul.html for general background). I found his class reasonably interesting, and got to understand his perspective somewhat better.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Ken Burns Teaches Documentary Filmmaking','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/ken-burns-teaches-documentary-filmmaking','2020-05-24','day','2020-07-11','day','I started watching this, then decided to take a detour to watch the Vietnam War documentary. I returned to this MasterClass after finishing the documentary. Overall, I liked the MasterClass and gained more appreciation of documentary filmmaking.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Doris Kearns Goodwin Teaches U.S. Presidential History and Leadership','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/doris-kearns-goodwin-teaches-us-presidential-history-and-leadership','2020-07-23','day','2020-08-22','day','I started watching this out of interest in history, and how a person with more positive views of politics might see that history. While I wasn''t persuaded, I did learn more about her way of thinking about history.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Shonda Rhimes Teaches Writing for Television','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/shonda-rhimes-teaches-writing-for-television','2020-08-22','day','2020-11-14','day','Having watched a few seasons of Scandal and a few episodes of Grey''s Anatomy, I was interested in what Shonda Rhimes, writer for both, had to say about her craft. Overall, it was a good MasterClass and I learned more about the perspective of a highly successful TV show writer.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Daniel Pink Teaches Sales and Persuasion','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/daniel-pink-teaches-sales-and-persuasion','2020-11-14','day','2020-11-15','day','I noticed this MasterClass because it was highlighted on the home page. I was interested in how Pink''s advice would agree and disagree with the advice from Chris Voss on negotiation. I generally liked it; I was impressed at the general level of agreement, with probably the only point of disagreement being the "Five Whys" technique.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Malcolm Gladwell Teaches Writing','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/malcolm-gladwell-teaches-writing','2020-11-15','day','2020-12-19','day','I had previously read and somewhat liked three of Gladwell''s books (The Tipping Point, Blink, and Outliers) and also read criticisms of Gladwell, most famously the "igon value problem" criticism. With these mixed feelings, I was curious to see how Gladwell described his own craft. Overall, I enjoyed the MasterClass and it gave me a greater appreciation of how Gladwell saw his craft, and the strengths and limitations of it.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Christina Aguilera Teaches Singing','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/christina-aguilera-teaches-singing','2020-12-19','day','2021-02-06','day','I had read a positive review of this MasterClass; I also have a lot of interest in music so I decided to watch this. The watching was somewhat interrupted by Netflix shows I was watching, but the pace of watching picked up when I let my Netflix subscription expire. I learned a lot of interesting facts and I really enjoyed the MasterClass.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Alicia Keys Teaches Songwriting and Producing','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/alicia-keys-teaches-songwriting-and-producing','2021-02-06','day','2021-02-14','day','After the Christina Aguilera MasterClass, my interest in music was piqued. Alicia Keys, who is also a singer but also a songwriter and composer, seemed like good for my next MasterClass. I enjoyed this MasterClass; the subject matter was more interesting to me than Christina Aguilera''s. I also enjoyed discovering two of her songs that she talked about in her MasterClass: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Urdlvw0SSEc (Fallin'') and https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rywUS-ohqeE (No One).'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Jon Kabat-Zinn Teaches Mindfulness and Meditation','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/jon-kabat-zinn-teaches-mindfulness-and-meditation','2021-02-14','day','2021-02-21','day','I saw this MasterClass highlighted on the homepage. I started watching it; my interest was also buoyed by the fact that the teacher was featured in https://timelines.issarice.com/wiki/Timeline_of_meditation that I had paid for a while back. I quite enjoyed it and grasped many more of the basics of meditation than I previously know, but I continue to consider meditation poor bang-for-the-buck for addressing emotional issues and achieving mental clarity. But I see that it is probably helpful once the "low-hanging fruit" have been addressed and one wants to continue to attain higher and higher levels of equanimity and tolerance for the vicissitudes of life. I skipped most of the lesson on the body scan.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Joe Holder Teaches Fitness and Wellness Fundamentals','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/joe-holder-teaches-fitness-and-wellness-fundamentals','2021-02-25','day','2021-03-01','day','I had of late been interested in fitness and wellness, partly as a result of watching some videos involving Ben Greenfield, and I saw this MasterClass featured on the home page. I found it quite good. Though the overall level of the exercises seems too advanced for me to immediately pursue, I learned and reinforced soem key paradigms around wellness, stress, and recovery.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Neil deGrasse Tyson Teaches Scientific Thinking and Communication','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/neil-degrasse-tyson-teaches-scientific-thinking-and-communication','2021-03-03','day','2021-03-04','day','Although I didn''t expect to learn a lot of new stuff, I thought it might be interesting. It was indeed reasonably fun for me although I didn''t learn a lot of new things.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Jane Goodall Teaches Conservation','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/jane-goodall-teaches-conservation','2021-03-03','day','2021-03-21','day','I was interested in this mainly for the animal cognition stuff. I stopped watching after the animal cognition part was over and the class switched over to conservation.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Emily Morse Teaches Sex and Communication','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/emily-morse-teaches-sex-and-communication','2021-04-03','day','2021-04-03','day','I was interested in this topic and saw it was short. Since my MasterClass subscription was ending in two days, I decided to watch it.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Penn & Teller Teach the Art of Magic','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/penn-and-teller-teach-the-art-of-magic','2021-04-03','day','2021-04-04','day','I was interested in this topic and saw it was short. Since my MasterClass subscription was ending in two days, I decided to watch it.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Hans Zimmer Teaches Film Scoring','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/hans-zimmer-teaches-film-scoring','2021-04-22','day','2021-05-14','day','I am quite interested in music and have been listening to several background themes of late. I saw Zimmer''s MasterClass featured on the home page and decided to try it out. I liked it quite a lot though it was slow going sometimes as I wanted to process the ideas.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Usher Teaches the Art of Performance','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/usher-teaches-the-art-of-performance','2021-05-19','day','2021-06-01','day','I watched this mainly because of its partial connection to music. I found it quite decent, but in general I''m finding fairly common themes across MasterClasses so some parts felt repetitive with other MasterClasses (not the fault of Usher!). There was also less by way of technical detail than some other MasterClasses had.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Aaron Sorkin Teaches Screenwriting','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/aaron-sorkin-teaches-screenwriting','2021-06-28','day','2021-07-12','day','I watched this after being intrigued by some of Aaron Sorkin''s work, despite considering it off-point in many ways, including The Social Network and Trial of the Chicago 7. I was also interested in comparing and contrasting Sorkin''s guidance with that of Shonda Rhimes, whose MasterClass I had watched a while back. I found his MasterClass quite interesting; particularly the workshop sessions including script readings, pitch sessions, and the West Wing writers'' room. I might write more about this later.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','St. Vincent Teaches Creativity and Songwriting','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/st-vincent-teaches-creativity-and-songwriting','2021-07-10','day','2021-07-28','day','I watched this MasterClass based on my general interest in music. I had not heard of St. Vincent or heard her songs before. Many themes repeated what I had already gathered from watching other music MasterClasses, but I did enjoy it quite a bit (more than Usher, that was also somewhat repetitive of previous MasterClasses). It was interesting to see the ''making of'' her song Savior, which I also liked after listening to it a few times.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Amy Tan Teaches Fiction, Memory, and Imagination','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/amy-tan-teaches-fiction-memory-and-imagination','2021-07-28','day','2021-08-06','day','I watched this MasterClass mostly out of general curiosity; I had previously read a bit about fiction-writing and I had vaguely heard of Amy Tan. It was reasonably interesting, and a good contrast to the screenwriting MasterClass from Aaron Sorkin and the related MasterClass from Shonda Rhimes.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','deadmau5 Teaches Electronic Music Production','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/deadmau5-teaches-electronic-music-production','2021-08-06','day','2021-08-23','day','I watched this MasterClass as part of my general interest in music, and specifically in electronic music editing (though I am not specifically interested in EDM). I had a chance to refresh my stems of knowledge about many topics related to music editing, as well as plant seeds for things I hope to learn in more detail in the future. Overall, I found it quite interesting! deadmau5 is quite opinionated, but seemed good about separating his personal takes from general factual knowledge.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Reba McEntire Teaches Country Music','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/reba-mcentire-teaches-country-music','2021-09-01','day','2021-09-24','day','I watched this MasterClass as part of my general interest in music. While there was quite an overlap with other music MasterClasses I had watched, the instructor''s greater age and therefore exposure to different historical periods lent different dimensions to this MasterClass. Overall, I found it worth the watch.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',true,'English','Madhur Jaffrey Teaches Indian Cooking','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/madhur-jaffrey-teaches-indian-cooking','2021-10-11','day','2021-10-11','day','I watched this MasterClass on a whim when looking for MasterClasses on cooking, as I''ve been interested of late in the various organizing principles of cooking.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Salman Rushdie Teaches Storytelling and Writing','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/salman-rushdie-teaches-storytelling-and-writing/','2021-09-30','day','2021-11-07','day','I watched this MasterClass out of a general interest/curiosity in Salman Rushdie''s work and in fiction-writing in general. I found it generally interesting and engaging, though of limited applicability to me. I had previously watched Amy Tan''s fiction-writing MasterClass so it was interesting to compare the two.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Itzhak Perlman Teaches Violin','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/itzhak-perlman-teaches-violin','2021-11-07','day','2021-11-16','day','I watched this MasterClass given my general interest in music, but my initial expectations were low as to how valuable it would be; I''m more interested in music composition than in playing instruments. However, I found the class to be unexpectedly useful in getting me to think more about various techniques used in playing musical instruments (such as legato, spiccato, vibrato, tremolo, etc.). The violin may be particularly suited for this given the many dimensions (degrees of freedom) involved, but I don''t know enough to judge. I found it interesting enough that I plan to consume the available MasterClasses on other instruments before my subscription runs out.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',false,'English','Carlos Santana Teaches the Art and Soul of Guitar','https://www.masterclass.com/classes/carlos-santana-teaches-the-art-and-soul-of-guitar','2021-11-16','day','2021-12-06','day','I watched this MasterClass right after Itzhak Perlman''s violin MasterClass; since that one had exceeded my expectations, I was interested in other MasterClasses about instruments. The two MasterClasses contrasted quite a bit; while Perlman was focused a lot more on technique and precision, Santana''s was more about how the music makes you feel. This probably reflects a bunch of differences: the kind of instruments they play (violins are more technically challenging), their roles (Perlman seems strictly an instrumentalist and Santana is more of a composer and freestyler), and their personalities. Overall I found Perlman''s more useful, but I appreciated both and felt the order of consumption was the right one.'),
  ('MasterClass','Series (such as TV show or web series)',true,'English','Chris Voss: Win Workplace Negotiations (Session)','https://www.masterclass.com/sessions/classes/win-workplace-negotiations','2021-12-25','day','2021-12-31','day','I watched this MasterClass session after seeing it advertised on the MasterClass home page for a while. I had already previously watched the Chris Voss MasterClass (see https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/CRAzG386t3suSqDgd/chris-voss-negotiation-masterclass-review for my lengthy review) and was interested to see how the session version differed. The session version was somewhat longer, and in most cases went into more detail on the techniques; it also covered a few additional techniques such as paraphrasing and summaries. It had many more demonstration videos that on the whole added a lot of value.');

